body.prompt:
Generate a fake conversation between a customer and an agent.
The agent should introduce themselves, their company and give the customer
their name. The agent should ask for the customer's name.
As part of the conversation, have the agent ask for two pieces of
personal information.  Spell out numbers. For example, 1000 should be
said as one zero zero zero, not one thousand. The conversation should be
at least 10 lines long and be complete. At the end
of the conversation, the agent should thank the customer for their time
and end the conversation. Return the conversation formatted 
like the following example:

{'conversation': 
    [
    {'speaker': 'Agent', 'message': 'xxxxx'}, 
    {'speaker': 'Customer', 'message': "xxxxx."}, 
    {'speaker': 'Agent', 'message': "xxxxxx"}
    ] 
}

body.speaker: Agent
body.message: Hello, thank you for reaching out to CarBiz Solutions. My name is Larry Williams. May I have your name, please?

body.speaker: Customer
body.message: Of course! My name is Ashley Lopez.

body.speaker: Agent
body.message: Nice to meet you, Ashley. To assist you further, could you provide the last four digits of your phone number?

body.speaker: Customer
body.message: Sure, it's seven zero two four.

body.speaker: Agent
body.message: Thank you, Ashley. I also need the first three characters of your email address.

body.speaker: Agent
body.message: Great, thank you for sharing that information. Is there anything else I can help you with today, Ashley?

body.speaker: Customer
body.message: Not at the moment, thank you. I'm feeling excited about the solutions you've provided.

body.speaker: Agent
body.message: I'm glad to hear that! Thank you for your time, Ashley. If you have any more questions in the future, feel free to reach out. Have a wonderful day!
